ApexComponentMember.name: ApexComponentMember
ApexComponentMember.description: Represents the working copy of a Visualforce component for editing, saving, or compiling in a MetadataContainer.

Body.description: The data for the Visualforce component. The Body field is the only field you can update() or PATCH.

Content.description: A string representation of ApexComponentMetadata that lists the version, status, and packaged versions of the corresponding Visualforce component.

ContentEntityId.description: A reference to a Visualforce component.There can be only one ContentEntityId per ApexComponentMember, otherwise, an error is reported. This field is required if FullName is not specified.

FullName.description: The full name of the associated object in the Metadata API. Use to avoid race conditions on create, before you have IDs.

LastSyncDate.description: The date that this ApexComponentMember Body was replicated from the underlying entity. When you deploy a MetadataContainer, this value is compared with the LastModifiedDate of the underlying Visualforce component. If LastSyncDate is older than LastModifiedDate, the deployment fails with an error.

Metadata.description: An object that describes the version, status, and packaged versions of the corresponding Visualforce component.

MetadataContainerId.description: A reference to a MetadataContainer or ContainerAsyncRequest object.As part of a successful deployment, this field is reset from the ID of the deployed MetadataContainer to the ID of the corresponding ContainerAsyncRequest object. This field is required.
